naher.com </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> If no Platform/ OpCo Legal Department </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> <a href=\"mailto:daniel.garen@danaher.com\">daniel.garen@danaher.com </a></span><br /><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Escalate the matter <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">before</span> investigating it&nbsp;</span></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 54px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 61.1264%; height: 54px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Environmental, Health and Safety (EHS) violations</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 38.8736%; height: 54px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Platform/OpCo Legal Department (if applicable) <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>And</strong></span> <br /> stephen.evanoff@danaher.com</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 54px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 61.1264%; vertical-align: top; height: 54px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Import, Export, Customs violations</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 38.8736%; height: 54px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Platform/OpCo Legal Department (if applicable) <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">And</span></strong> <br /> daniel.garen@danaher.com</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 288px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 61.1264%; height: 288px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Litigation /Arbitration/Subpoenas</span></strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Lawsuit, arbitration demand, or claim by or against OpCo if:</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> amount at issue &gt; $250k</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> IP involved (patents, trademarks, copyrights, trade secrets)</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> important product or market opportunity at issue</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> reputational damage to OpCo or DHR possible</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> a government agency or state-owned company is a party</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> business relationships with other OpCos could be affected</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> injunctive/declaratory/equitable relief, class action claims</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> substantial risk of material or meritorious counterclaims  Subpoena or other service of process received  Approval needed from DHR Legal prior to:</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> any threat or claim against a third party (excluding simple collections or enforcing rights against former associates)</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> engaging outside counsel if legal spend &gt;$25K (no OpCo Legal Department), or &gt;$100K (with OpCo Legal Department)</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 38.8736%; vertical-align: top; height: 288px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Notify</span></strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Platform/OpCo Legal Department (if applicable) <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>And</strong></span></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> mary.britton@danaher.com</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> If no Platform/OpCo Legal Department</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> mary.britton@danaher.com</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Do not hire private investigators without consulting Platform/OpCo Legal Department.</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 54px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 61.1264%; height: 54px; vertical-align: top;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Labor, employment, restrictive covenant matters</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 38.8736%; height: 54px; vertical-align: top;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Platform/OpCo Legal Department (if applicable) And  patricia.kim@danaher.com</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 216px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 61.1264%; height: 216px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">EHS Incidents <br />Any of the following at an OpCo facility or in work-related field activities:  fire <br /> fatality <br /> workplace incident or driving-related injury on company business requiring hospital admission or resulting in other serious injury, e.g., amputation, broken bone, loss of consciousness <br /> widespread exposure to toxic or potentially harmful materials/chemicals above regulatory limits or in excess of health standards <br /> acts of nature that result in major facility damage or business interruption of more than one week <br /> environmental contamination, unpermitted releases, or spills of hazardous materials that significantly interrupt operations or impact the community</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 38.8736%; vertical-align: top; height: 216px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Notify <br /> Platform/OpCo Legal Department and EHSOLC representative (if applicable) And one of the following <br /> <a href=\"mailto:stephen.evanoff@danaher.com\">stephen.evanoff@danaher.com </a><br /> mary.britton@danaher.com</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<br pagebreak=\"true\"/>\r\n<table style=\"border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; height: 162px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 144px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 61.5385%; height: 144px; vertical-align: top;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Media Inquires</span></strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Non-trade media and press inquiries</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Do not speak to non-trade media and press before talking to Investor Relations.</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 38.4615%; height: 144px; vertical-align: top;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Notify</span></strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Investor Relations</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> matt.gugino@danaher.com</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> If legal/regulatory aspect, copy Platform/OpCo Legal</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Department (if applicable) And</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> jim.o&rsquo;reilly@danaher.com</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> mary.britton@danaher.com</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 18px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 61.5385%; height: 18px; vertical-align: top;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Cyber Security Events</span></strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Receipt of fraudulent or impersonating electronic messages that attempt to use authority to wire transfer Danaher funds to a non- standard account</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Attempts to commit fraud that would result in financial loss through misrepresentation &amp; impersonation in e-mail, instant messaging, phone call and/or other digital means</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> All &ldquo;spear phishing&rdquo; cyber attacks involving company assets and information.</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 38.4615%; height: 18px; vertical-align: top;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Notify</span></strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Security Leader</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> chris.lugo@danaher.com</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Platform IT Leader/Manager</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> Platform/OpCo Legal Department (if applicable) Legal must notify:</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"> daniel.garen@danaher.com</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 23, 24, 1, '2019-03-28 05:39:13', '2019-03-28 05:41:06', 1, NULL, 1, NULL),
(94, 'How to Request time off', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>How to Request Time Off?<br /></strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Log into ADP:</strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong><a href=\"https://portal.adp.com\">https://portal.adp.com</a><br /><img src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/request_time_off.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"565\" height=\"240\" /><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>Go to My Request:</strong> Click on the my request header with your left mouse key and drag into the center of the screen.<br /><img src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/request_time_off_1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"705\" height=\"442\" /><br /></span></p>\r\n<br pagebreak=\"true\"/>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">When my request is in the center of your screen change the Time period to include the time period you are requesting. Example is you like 12/23 off make sure the date range includes 12/23 date.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">After you change the time period please hit the &ldquo;Apply&rdquo; button and the calendar will be updated.<br /><img src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/request_time_off__2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"707\" height=\"469\" /><br /></span></p>\r\n<br pagebreak=\"true\"/>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Go to the bottom left and select &ldquo;Time off request 8 hours per day&rdquo;<br /></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">A new box will appear to the left.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">1) Enter your start and end date. Remember do not request weekend or holidays as vacation, eTime will charge your account for them. If you have a vacation that runs over a weekend two request need to be entered.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">2) Make sure the paycode is what you are requesting. (Vacation, sick, etc&hellip;)</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">3) Then submit your request</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><img src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/request_time_off___3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"710\" height=\"418\" /><br /></span></p>\r\n<br pagebreak=\"true\"/>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">After you submit your request your calendar will be updated with your request. It should read &ldquo;Whole(submitted)&rdquo;. Meaning the whole day has been submitted to your manager.<br /></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">You will also see that now you have current request out there</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><img src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/request_time_off___4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"710\" height=\"424\" /></span></p>', 23, 24, 1, '2019-03-28 06:16:43', '2019-03-28 06:22:09', 1, NULL, 1, NULL),
(95, 'Rental Car Guidelines', '<p><img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/leica.png\" alt=\"leica logo\" width=\"84\" height=\"60\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Rental car guideline</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">1. Rental car bookings</span></strong><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Avis is the preferred rental car company for Leica Biosystems and shall be used for all rental car </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">bookings (through BCD or direct). Exceptions are only allowed if Avis rent is not available or other </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">providers are cheaper.<br /></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Information on the Avis program can be found here:</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">https://www.danaherconnect. co m/t ravel/PaKes/Rentaf-Car-lnfo.aspx</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br />Register for Avis preferred: httDs://www.danaherconnect.com/travel/Pages/Hertz.asDx</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br /><strong>2. Rental car best practice</strong></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">To avoid any extra cost on rental cars, make sure you provide the guidelines below to your travelers:</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">* Book the appropriate car dass.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Danaher only allows economy, compact or intermediate/midsize cars. Exceptions might </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">occur if more than 3 people travel together (with luggage)</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">* Check the rental car for any defects, scratches, dings, cracks, etc and report those before </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">departure.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">* Mark any defect found on the rental agreement and get it signed by a representative of </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">the rental car company.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Warning: Not all markets are the same. Whiie the US is a bit more generous on little </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">scratches, other markets (e.g. Germany) are very fussy on any type of defects and have </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">a rigorous check on the return, especially at airports. Airport services are typically outsourced </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">and it is in the interest of the service provider to identify any additional revenue</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">stream through damages.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">* Decline prepaid gas options (rent filled car and return empty).</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Any unused gas remaining in the tank is a \"gift\" to the rental car company.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">* Fill up the car before returning.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Rental car companies charge up to 3 times or more of the market price for a liter of gas </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">to be refilled through their staff</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">* Follow the iaw - avoid traffic violations</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">In addition to the cost of the ticket, there is an up charge through the rental car company </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">(could be 30&euro; or more per incident), in addition, your company gets notified.</span></p>\r\n<br pagebreak=\"true\"/>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10px;\">Handout Corporate Customer Standard Procedure</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Information for Rental car users</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Receiving the car:</span></strong><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">To ensure a safe and satisfying rental, you will be served with a welf-checked car. The car </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">will be handed over to you in a proper and roadworthy condition, inside the car you will find </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">the car paper, the green insurance card and an Avis Budget Accident/! ncident report form.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">During the winter month, the level of antifreeze is sufficient and an ice scraper is available in </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">every car. In addition, all our cars will be also equipped with winter-tires from November until </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">March.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">The rental station or the delivering service staff will hand out to you an rental agreement. If </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">the car has any known chargeable damages, they are stated on the car picture either printed </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">or added manual.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Due to the monetary responsibility of the renter for all new damages, you should always </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">check the car before starting your trip, Just take a walk around: If there are any damages </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">that are not mentioned on your rental agreement, you can prevent rental charges or </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">misunderstandings by reporting them directly to the service staff or to the rental station by</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">phone.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><br /><strong>Example for an opening rental agreement:<br /><img src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/rental_car.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"659\" height=\"446\" /><br /></strong></span></p>\r\n<br pagebreak=\"true\"/>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10px;\">Handout Corporate Customer Standard Procedure</span><br /></span><br /><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">During your rental:</span></strong><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">in case of a breakdown, accident or any incident like theft, collision with a stationary object, </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">parking damage, lost equipment, etc., you should always use the accident/incident report </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">form, follow the instructions of the rental agreement and inform the rental station/assistance </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">hotline immediately. To protect your interests you should always ask any involved third party </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">for their green card and for all the details to fill out the accident report form, including</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">signature. Please note that only a police report can establish that a third party has caused </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">the accident.<br /></span><br /><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Returning the car:</span></strong><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">At every collection or returning of a car, the service staff will check it for new damages, in </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">general Avis does not charge for fair wear and tear resulting from normal use of its vehicles </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">like:</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">&bull; Superficial abrasions which can be polished out without special equipment</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">&bull; Scratches tess than 25mm which do not penetrate the paint surface</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">&bull; Dents less than 25mm with no paint cracking or flaking</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">&bull; Stone chips less than 5mm without denting</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">&bull; Chip marks to glass which do not penetrate the first layer</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">&bull; Wheel or wheel trim scuffs without cracking or gouging</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">All other damages are chargeable and have to be recorded, regardless whether they will be </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">charged to you or not.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">You can follow the checking procedure quite easiiy and it only takes 2 minutes (excluding </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">the time for completing the incident/accident report form, of course). The vehicle should </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">always be assessed according to the Group standard, applying the 14 points check and the </span><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">standard viewing angle from different heights.<br /></span><br /><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">14 points check:<br /><img src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/rental_car_1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"518\" height=\"299\" /><br /></span></strong></p>\r\n<br pagebreak=\"true\"/>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10px;\">Handout Corporate Customer Standard Procedure<br /></span><br /><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Indications for chargeable damages:<br /><img src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/rental_car_2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"696\" height=\"507\" /><br /></span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><strong>After the rental:</strong><br />The damage costs are charged up to the contractually agreed maximum excess, via the method of payment mentioned on the rental agreement. Your claim documents are available on request from our customer service.<br />If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact the damage department of our customer service. Contact details are shown on the rental agreement.<br /><strong>Special case:</strong> If the damage has been caused by a third party, we claim the costs from the person responsible. As soon as the other party\'s fault has been clearly established, any damage costs that may have been charged to you are reimbursed.<br />in case of issues or questions, send an e-mail to: travei-issue@leicabiosystems.com</span></p>', 23, 24, 1, '2019-03-28 07:10:51', '2019-03-28 07:14:07', 1, NULL, 1, NULL),
(96, 'Workday - How to Guide Leaflet', '<p><img src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/workday_1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1069\" height=\"1523\" /></p>\r\n<br pagebreak=\"true\"/>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/workday_2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1075\" height=\"1539\" /></p>', 23, 24, 1, '2019-03-28 07:26:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 1, NULL, 1, NULL),
(97, 'President_s Welcome Letter LBS', '<p><img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/leica.png\" alt=\"leica logo\" width=\"98\" height=\"70\" /><br />Advancing Cancer Diagnostics<br />Improving Livs</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Welcome to Leica Biosystems</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">I would like to personally welcome you to Leica Biosystems (&ldquo;LBS&rdquo;), a Danaher Operating Company. We are excited that you have chosen to be part of our team. We truly believe our associates are our biggest asset. As we say in Danaher, &ldquo;Best Team Wins.&rdquo;</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">At LBS, our mission is Advancing Cancer Diagnostics, Improving Lives. We are proud to be the only company that owns the workflow from biopsy to diagnosis. What we do truly has an impact on people&rsquo;s lives &ndash; from the moment a person suspects they or a loved one has cancer to the point when they are given a treatment strategy. We are committed to delivering products around the world that will make our customers more effective thus enhancing the care they provide to their patients.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Through our Performance for Growth (&ldquo;P4G&rdquo;), Development for Growth (&ldquo;D4G&rdquo;) and Danaher Go processes, we offer the opportunity for associates to grow their careers and achieve their career aspirations through LBS and Danaher. I encourage you to learn about these processes and to utilize them to have a successful career at LBS and Danaher.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Embrace the Danaher Business System. The Danaher Business System (DBS) is our proven system for achieving success at Danaher. It drives every aspect of our culture and performance. We use DBS to guide what we do, measure how well we execute, and drive a continuous cycle of change and improvement. DBS is &ndash; and will continue to be &ndash; the key factor that differentiates us from our competitors.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Onboarding is critical to your success. I urge you to learn the business and understand our market and our customers. We take great pride in our knowledge of our markets. Our customer&rsquo;s problems can only be solved if we have a deep understanding of their business and their challenges.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">As you begin your new professional journey with Leica Biosystems, I encourage you to embrace our culture. Learn everything you can; ask questions, challenge yourself, get involved and feel empowered.<br /></span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Again, welcome to LBS.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://nap.bluenettech.com/assets/img/president_sign.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"175\" height=\"59\" /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">Melissa Aquino<br />President, Leica Biosystems<br /></span></p>', 15, 1, 1, '2019-03-28 08:59:36', '2019-03-28 09:26:29', 1, NULL, 1, NULL);
